      "content": "If a train is late, you're right to be worried; delays are the biggest headache in this kind of journey. Things that usually mess up the timing are the baggage claim at Heathrow, the sheer chaos of navigating Paddington station, and the unpredictable nature of the LNER service itself. It's a good idea to factor in an extra 30 minutes specifically for unexpected delays, just in case. Always keep your tickets handy, or you'll be stuck waiting around, which is the worst.",
      "source": "target",
